{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/algorithm/8-group-anagrams/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Soobing","author":"[Soobin Bak]","siteUrl":"https://soobing.netlify.com","comment":{"disqusShortName":"","utterances":"soobing/soobing.github.io"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":"soobing"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e1155884-b78e-59b7-b014-d194646bcddd","excerpt":"오늘은 30-Day LeetCoding Challenge Week1 마감 데이이다🔥그래서 부랴부랴 밀린 3문제를 모두 풀어보았다! 이번 포스팅에서는 anagrams와 관련된 문제풀이를 해보도록 하겠다.  문제 요약 anagrams은 단어를 구성하는 알파벳을 재배열해서 새로운 단어를 만들 수 있는 것을 말한다. 그래서 문제의 예시처럼 “eat”, “tea”, “ate”는 하나의 anagrams 그룹으로 묶을 수 있다. 문제 해결 anagram…","html":"<p>오늘은 30-Day LeetCoding Challenge Week1 마감 데이이다🔥그래서 부랴부랴 밀린 3문제를 모두 풀어보았다! 이번 포스팅에서는 <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/explore/challenge/card/30-day-leetcoding-challenge/528/week-1/3288/\">anagrams</a>와 관련된 문제풀이를 해보도록 하겠다.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1200px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"anagrams\"\n        title=\"anagrams\"\n        src=\"/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/e5166/group-anagrams.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/f93b5/group-anagrams.jpg 300w,\n/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/b4294/group-anagrams.jpg 600w,\n/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/e5166/group-anagrams.jpg 1200w,\n/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/c58a3/group-anagrams.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h1 id=\"문제-요약\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EB%AC%B8%EC%A0%9C-%EC%9A%94%EC%95%BD\" aria-label=\"문제 요약 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>문제 요약</h1>\n<p>anagrams은 단어를 구성하는 알파벳을 재배열해서 새로운 단어를 만들 수 있는 것을 말한다. 그래서 문제의 예시처럼 “eat”, “tea”, “ate”는 하나의 anagrams 그룹으로 묶을 수 있다.</p>\n<h1 id=\"문제-해결\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EB%AC%B8%EC%A0%9C-%ED%95%B4%EA%B2%B0\" aria-label=\"문제 해결 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>문제 해결</h1>\n<p>anagram인지는 어떻게 판단하면 좋을까? 단어를 구성하는 알파벳을 순서대로 정렬한 다음 비교해보면 될 것이다. <code class=\"language-text\">s.split(&#39;&#39;).sort().join(&#39;&#39;)</code> 이렇게! 문제에서 anagram이 있는지 찾는지를 어떻게 구현할지도 생각해 봐야하는데, key값으로 <code class=\"language-text\">구성하는 알파벳을 순서대로 정렬한 값</code>을 저장해서 판단하도록 하면된다. 이것이 가장 심플하고 복잡도도 낮다.</p>\n<p>실제로 leetcode solution을 보면 </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Approach 1: Categorize by Sorted String</li>\n<li>Approach 2: Categorize by Count\n두 가지가 있는데, JS의 map을 이용하면 Approach 1로 쉽게 풀 수 있고, Approach 2는 크게 매력적인 해결책이 아니어서 패스하도록한다.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"1-categorize-by-sorted-string\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-categorize-by-sorted-string\" aria-label=\"1 categorize by sorted string permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1) Categorize by Sorted String</h2>\n<p>위에서 이야기 했듯이 단어를 구성하는 알파벳을 순서대로 정렬한 다음 key값으로 저장하여 비교한다.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">/**\n * @param {string[]} strs\n * @return {string[][]}\n */</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">groupAnagrams</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">strs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> map <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">getKey</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">s</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> s<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">split</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">join</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> item <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> strs<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> key <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">getKey</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>map<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>key<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            map<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>key<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            map<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">set</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>key<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>map<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">values</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"소감\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EC%86%8C%EA%B0%90\" aria-label=\"소감 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>소감</h1>\n<p>사실 위의 해결책은 내 코드는 아니었고, 검색하다가 다른사람의 코드를 참고했다.\n나는 정말 if를 떡칠하면서 오랜 시간동안 문제를 해결하지 못했다. 너무 오랫동안 고민해서 그런가 저 코드를 보고 엄청나게 충격적이었다. 너무 심플해서 🤯\n그치만 덕분에 다음문제를 내 스스로 풀 수 있었다.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"🏵 Group Anagrams","date":"April 07, 2020","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"src":"/static/7bad5b02eebea216abc689274b9d3706/14b42/group-anagrams.jpg"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/algorithm/8-group-anagrams/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/algorithm/7-best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-2/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"📈 Best Time To Buy and Sell Stock 2","category":"algorithm","draft":false}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/algorithm/9-counting-elements/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"🏄‍♂️ Counting Elements","category":"algorithm","draft":false}}}}}